Use the correct URL: 
https://tile.openstreetmap.org/{z}/{x}/{y}.png

Z (Zoom): Represents the zoom level. A value of 0 shows the entire world on a single tile, while higher numbers zoom in closer (e.g., zoom level 19 shows individual buildings). At zoom level z, the total map is a grid of \(2^z \times 2^z\) tiles.

X (Column): Represents the horizontal position. It starts at 0 on the 180° meridian (west) and counts up as you move east.

Y (Row): Represents the vertical position. It starts at 0 at the northernmost edge of the map and counts down as you move south

